trans-unit.source: Installs an executable containing classes that extend <xref href="System.ServiceProcess.ServiceBase"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Installerer en kjørbar fil som inneholder klasser som utvide <xref href="System.ServiceProcess.ServiceBase"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: This class is called by installation utilities, such as InstallUtil.exe, when installing a service application.
trans-unit.target: Denne klassen kalles av installasjonen, for eksempel InstallUtil.exe,-verktøy når du installerer et tjenesteprogram.

trans-unit.source: The ServiceProcessInstaller does work common to all services in an executable.
trans-unit.target: ServiceProcessInstaller fungerer felles for alle tjenester i en kjørbar fil.

trans-unit.source: It is used by the installation utility to write registry values associated with services you want to install.
trans-unit.target: Den brukes av installasjonen-verktøyet til å skrive registerverdier som er knyttet til tjenestene du vil installere.

trans-unit.source: To install a service, create a project installer class that inherits from <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer>, and set the <xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute> on the class to `true`.
trans-unit.target: For å installere en tjeneste, kan du opprette et prosjekt installasjonsprogrammet klassen som arver fra <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer>, og angi den <xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute>på klassen for å `true`.</xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute> </xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer>

trans-unit.source: Within your project, instantiate one ServiceProcessInstaller instance per service application, and one <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller> instance for each service in the application.
trans-unit.target: I prosjektet, kan du starte én ServiceProcessInstaller forekomst per tjenesteprogrammet, og én <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>forekomsten for hver tjeneste i applikasjonen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>

trans-unit.source: Finally, add the ServiceProcessInstaller instance and the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller> instances to your project installer class.
trans-unit.target: Legg til slutt ServiceProcessInstaller-forekomst og - <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>forekomster til klasse. installer den prosjektet</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>

trans-unit.source: When InstallUtil.exe runs, the utility looks for classes in the service assembly with the <xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute> set to `true`.
trans-unit.target: Når InstallUtil.exe kjører, verktøyet ser etter klasser i service-samling med den <xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute>satt til `true`.</xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute>

trans-unit.source: Add classes to the service assembly by adding them to the <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Installers%2A> collection associated with your project installer.
trans-unit.target: Legg til klasser service-samlingen ved å legge dem til i <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Installers%2A>samling tilknyttet prosjektet-installer.</xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Installers%2A>

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute> is `false`, the install utility ignores the project installer.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute>er `false`, installer verktøyet ignorerer installasjonsprogrammet for prosjektet.</xref:System.ComponentModel.RunInstallerAttribute>

trans-unit.source: For an instance of ServiceProcessInstaller, properties you can modify include specifying that a service application run under an account other than the logged-on user.
trans-unit.target: En forekomst av ServiceProcessInstaller inkludere egenskaper kan du endre angir som et tjenesteprogram kjører under en annen konto enn den påloggede brukeren.

trans-unit.source: You can specify a particular <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> pair under which the service should run, or you can use <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> to specify that the service run under the computer's System account, a local or network service account, or a user account.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi en bestemt <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>paret tjenesten må kjøre som, eller du kan bruke <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A>til å angi at tjenesten kjører under datamaskinens System-kontoen, en lokal eller Nettverkstjeneste eller en brukerkonto.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The computer's System account is not the same as the Administrator account.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Datamaskinens System-kontoen er ikke det samme som administratorkonto.

trans-unit.source: Normally, you do not call the methods on <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller> within your code; they are generally called only by the install utility.
trans-unit.target: Vanligvis du ikke kaller metodene på <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>i koden; de vanligvis kalles bare av Installer verktøyet.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>

trans-unit.source: The install utility automatically calls the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Install%2A?displayProperty=fullName> and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller.Install%2A?displayProperty=fullName> methods during the installation process.
trans-unit.target: Installer verktøyet automatisk kaller den <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Install%2A?displayProperty=fullName>og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller.Install%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metoder under installasjonen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller.Install%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Install%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: It backs out failures, if necessary, by calling <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Rollback%2A> (or <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller.Rollback%2A?displayProperty=fullName>) on all previously installed components.
trans-unit.target: Det tar ut feil, hvis nødvendig ved å kalle <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Rollback%2A>(eller <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller.Rollback%2A?displayProperty=fullName>) på alle installerte komponenter.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller.Rollback%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Rollback%2A>

trans-unit.source: An application's install routine maintains information automatically about the components already installed, using the project installer's <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Et program Installer rutinen opprettholder informasjon automatisk om komponenter allerede er installert, ved hjelp av prosjektet installasjonsprogrammets <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: This state information is continuously updated as the ServiceProcessInstaller instance and each <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller> instance is installed by the utility.
trans-unit.target: Denne statusinformasjon oppdateres kontinuerlig ServiceProcessInstaller forekomsten og hver <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>forekomsten er installert av verktøyet.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceInstaller>

trans-unit.source: It is usually unnecessary for your code to modify this state information explicitly.
trans-unit.target: Det er vanligvis unødvendige for koden til å endre denne statusinformasjon eksplisitt.

trans-unit.source: Instantiating a ServiceProcessInstaller causes the base class constructor, <xref:System.Configuration.Install.ComponentInstaller.%23ctor%2A>, to be called.
trans-unit.target: Start av en ServiceProcessInstaller fører til at basisklassen-konstruktøren <xref:System.Configuration.Install.ComponentInstaller.%23ctor%2A>du kalles.</xref:System.Configuration.Install.ComponentInstaller.%23ctor%2A>

trans-unit.source: Creates a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the type of account under which to run this service application.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir hvilken type konto som du vil kjøre dette programmet under.

trans-unit.source: When the Account property is `User`, the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> properties are used to define an account under which the service application runs.
trans-unit.target: Når egenskapen Account er `User`, <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>Egenskaper brukes til å definere en konto som tjenesteprogrammet kjører under.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> pair allows the service to run under an account other than the system account.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>paret, kan tjenesten kjøre under en annen konto enn systemkontoen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: This can, for example, allow the service to start automatically at reboot, when no user is logged on.
trans-unit.target: Dette kan for eksempel at tjenesten skal starte automatisk ved omstart, når ingen bruker er logget på.

trans-unit.source: If you leave either the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> or <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> empty and set Account to `User`, you will be prompted for a valid user name and password at installation.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du forlater enten den <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>eller <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>tom og konfigurere konto `User`, du blir bedt om å angi et gyldig brukernavn og passord på installasjonen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: You can also specify that the service run under the local system account, or as a local or network service.
trans-unit.target: Du kan også angi at tjenesten kjøre under den lokale systemkontoen eller som en lokal eller Nettverkstjeneste.

trans-unit.source: See the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceAccount> enumeration for details on types of accounts.
trans-unit.target: Se den <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceAccount>-nummerering for informasjon om kontotyper.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceAccount>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.ServiceProcess.ServiceAccount"></xref> that defines the type of account under which the system runs this service.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.ServiceProcess.ServiceAccount"> </xref> som definerer hvilken type konto systemet kjøres under denne tjenesten.

trans-unit.source: The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_User" name="User" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Standard <xref uid="langword_csharp_User" name="User" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The Password and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> pair allows the service to run under an account other than the system account.
trans-unit.target: Passordet og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>paret, kan tjenesten kjøre under en annen konto enn systemkontoen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: This can, for example, allow the service to start automatically at reboot, when no user is logged on.
trans-unit.target: Dette kan for eksempel at tjenesten skal starte automatisk ved omstart, når ingen bruker er logget på.

trans-unit.source: Password and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> are handled in a secure manner in that they are never serialized or saved to the install state (the project installer's <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName>) or other location with public access.
trans-unit.target: Passord og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>behandles på en sikker måte ved at de er aldri serialisert eller lagres i installasjonsstatus (installasjonsprogrammet for prosjektet <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName>) eller en annen plassering med public-tilgang.</xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: Setting the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> and Password allows an account to be associated automatically with the service at install time.
trans-unit.target: Angivelse av <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>og passord gjør det mulig for en konto som skal knyttes til automatisk tjenesten under installasjonen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: If you leave either the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> or Password empty and set <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> to `User`, you will be prompted for a valid user name and password at installation.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du forlater enten den <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>eller passordet tom og angitt <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A>til `User`, du blir bedt om å angi et gyldig brukernavn og passord på installasjonen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>

trans-unit.source: Another option for running a service under a separate account is to use the computer's System account.
trans-unit.target: Et annet alternativ for å kjøre en tjeneste under en egen konto er å bruke datamaskinens System-kontoen.

trans-unit.source: That account, which is distinct from the Administrator account, requires no password.
trans-unit.target: Denne kontoen, som er forskjellig fra administratorkontoen, krever passord.

trans-unit.source: The System account's privileges may exceed those of the user currently logged in.
trans-unit.target: Den systemkontoen rettigheter, kan overskride i den påloggede brukeren.

trans-unit.source: Running under the System account rather than a user account avoids problems resulting from the user lacking a permission the service requires If <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> is any value other than `User`, the specifed account (local or network service, or local system) is used, even if the <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> and Password properties are populated.
trans-unit.target: Kjører under systemkontoen i stedet for en brukerkonto forhindrer problemer som et resultat av brukeren mangler en tillatelse tjenesten krever Hvis <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A>har en annen verdi enn `User`, angitt-konto (lokalt eller Nettverkstjeneste eller lokalt system) brukes, selv om den <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A>og egenskaper for passord er utfylt.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Username%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A>

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the user account under which the service application will run.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir brukerkontoen som tjenesteprogrammet skal kjøres.

trans-unit.source: The Username and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> pair allows the service to run under an account other than the system account.
trans-unit.target: Brukernavnet og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>paret, kan tjenesten kjøre under en annen konto enn systemkontoen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>

trans-unit.source: This can, for example, allow the service to start automatically at reboot, when no user is logged on.
trans-unit.target: Dette kan for eksempel at tjenesten skal starte automatisk ved omstart, når ingen bruker er logget på.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> and Username are handled in a secure manner in that they are never serialized or saved to the install state (the project installer's <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName>) or other location with public access.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>og brukernavnet håndteres på en sikker måte ved at de er aldri serialisert eller lagres i installasjonsstatus (installasjonsprogrammet for prosjektet <xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName>) eller en annen plassering med public-tilgang.</xref:System.Configuration.Install.Installer.Context%2A?displayProperty=fullName></xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>

trans-unit.source: Setting the Username and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> allows an account to be associated automatically with the service at install time.
trans-unit.target: Angi brukernavnet og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>gjør det mulig for en konto som skal knyttes til automatisk tjenesten under installasjonen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>

trans-unit.source: If you leave either the Username or <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> empty and set <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> to `User`, you will be prompted for a valid user name and password at installation.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du forlater enten brukernavnet eller <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>tom og angitt <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A>til `User`, du blir bedt om å angi et gyldig brukernavn og passord på installasjonen.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>

trans-unit.source: Another option for running a service under a separate account is to use the computer's System account.
trans-unit.target: Et annet alternativ for å kjøre en tjeneste under en egen konto er å bruke datamaskinens System-kontoen.

trans-unit.source: That account, which is distinct from the Administrator account, requires no password.
trans-unit.target: Denne kontoen, som er forskjellig fra administratorkontoen, krever passord.

trans-unit.source: The System account's privileges may exceed those of the user currently logged in.
trans-unit.target: Den systemkontoen rettigheter, kan overskride i den påloggede brukeren.

trans-unit.source: Running under the System account rather than a user account avoids problems resulting from the user lacking a permission the service requires If <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A> is any value other than `User`, the specified account (local or network service, or local system) is used, even if the Username and <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> properties are populated.
trans-unit.target: Kjører under systemkontoen i stedet for en brukerkonto forhindrer problemer som et resultat av brukeren mangler en tillatelse tjenesten krever Hvis <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A>har en annen verdi enn `User`, brukes den angitte kontoen (lokal eller Nettverkstjeneste eller lokalt system), selv om brukernavnet og <xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A>Egenskaper er utfylt.</xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Password%2A> </xref:System.ServiceProcess.ServiceProcessInstaller.Account%2A>

trans-unit.source: The account under which the service should run.
trans-unit.target: Kontoen som tjenesten skal kjøres.

trans-unit.target: Standarden er en tom streng ("").
